I was riding south on S. Irving St., coming to a stop at the stop sign at 2nd St. S. A driver made a left from 2nd St. S. northbound on S. Irving St. He turned into the wrong side of S. Irving St. (his left) almost hitting me before he swerved right to miss me.

column21: Driver aggressive and turned around to blow his horn.

column10: Three middle school girls were walking home, just in front of me, after school ended. They were in the crosswalk and a woman driving a car eastbound was driving quickly and recklessly. She saw them midway through the street at the last moment and slammed on the brakes, narrowly missing the girls. The driver was clearly rattled at how close she was to striking them. Close calls involving children happen frequently at this crosswalk despite signage.
